-----
Piton
-----

Formal models for identity- and capability-based reasoning on the web.

Files:

naturals.als

  Describes natural numbers (used to represent time)

caps.als

  The main definitions of capability-based interactions.  Defines what
  a CapServer is, and the various operations that can be performed on
  one.

examples.als

  Sanity tests for caps.als.  Ensures that the various operations can
  be performed, and will have more basic assertions added.

echo-server.als

  Defines a server that responds to all invocations with exactly the
  arguments that were supplied.
